title: For Sale:  Barrett M107A1 29" FDE 50 BMG QDL Suppressor
postcontent:
BARRETT M107A1 !! 

The Barrett M107A1 .50 BMG semi-automatic rifle is an exceptional firearm! Here are some of the new upgrades: 

* It has the upgraded muzzle brake which gives you less recoil, and enables you to stay on target for faster, more accurate follow up shots. The new 4 chamber muzzlebrake is also able to receive their quick attach suppressor if you ever wanted to silence your 50. (Barrett has said that currently the new muzzlebrake is not available as a separate accessory for the M82A1). 

* It's made of a much stronger, lighter titanium, so even though it's very light it's more durable, and the titanium w/ the upgraded brake keeps recoil down. Also aluminum and steel areas where possible have been thinned for further weight savings without sacrificing the integrity of the design. 

* The mags are much better with a tougher finish, and the mag has sight holes so you can tell exactly how many rounds you have left; our customers that hunt w/ their .50's love that feature, and our troops demand it. 

* The finish on the M107's is much more durable, scratch resistant and rust resistant. 

* It has the thermal cheek guard that allows the shooter to rest their face on the cheek plate and not directly on metal. Also, it's elevated which is ideal because the M107A1 has a really long, elevated mono-rail. 

* It has a lightweight, quick detach bipod with modular feet. 

* It has a monopod as standard equipment instead of having to pay additional and add as an accessory; this is a big help so you do not have to support the weight of the rear of the rifle with your own strength. It also allows you to dial the elevation of where your aiming up or down with the monopod with even more accuracy so even if you don't want to upgrade you may want to ask about adding a monopod. 

*The case it comes with from the factory is an upgrade from a Pelican case to a nicer Storm case. The Storm case is much easier to open and close, and you don’t bust your knuckles on it, and the case features padding inside instead of bare plastic. 

*More potential investment value as it has the same rollmark as our military gets, with the M107A1 designation. We see with our Knights Armament Rifles, Schmidt & Bender scopes, Remington Defense rifles, etc. that military markings always drive up price further down the road when the rifles are no longer offered.

title: For Sale:  NICE Swedish Mauser M94/14  6.5x55
postcontent:
For sale is a sporterized Swedish Mauser M94/14 in the classic 6.5 x 55 caliber. Interarms, long ago, imported a number of these hard to find classics. To identify these carbines as "theirs", they scrubbed the year of manufacture commonly found on the breech and roll marked "Interarms G33/50".

The barrel is 18 inches long making this ideal for those of you who brush hunt deer, etc. Add maneuverability to the legendary accuracy of the 6.5 x 55 cartridge and what's not to like.

The action rests in a sporterized Mauser stock as you can see from the photos. The receiver has NOT been drilled or tapped, it's in its as original condition. Magazine capacity is 5 rounds and this is one caliber that hasn't gone through the roof in terms of ammunition prices.

The action, bolt, shroud, and safety are all matching numbers. I've fired this rifle, it's accurate as all get out even with the iron sights and fun to shoot.

I've got some taxes to pay and, if you have any familiarity with Swedish Mausers you'll see that the price is quite attractive as stated. Not interested in any trades at this time.

Cash is king. I live in the NW burbs of Milwaukee and will drive up to 30 minutes if you're a serious buyer. Drop me an email with any questions and we'll go from there. I have additional photos if you're interested.

postcontent:

The Ruger 10/22 is one of the most popular 22 rifles in the world and many types of scopes and mounts are available for this handy little carbine. Many of the compact and mini-scopes being manufactured today rival the performance of full size scopes while offering lighter weight and smaller profiles. These features make them ideal for rim fire and other small caliber sporting rifles and, even though the eye relief on these mini-scopes equals that of the full size scopes, they do present a problem. Because of their short length, they need to be mounted further back on the receiver.

Most Weaver style scope mounts were made for full size scopes on high power rifles and don’t work well on smaller 22s. Until recently, there were few mounts made that could effectively accommodate the smaller mini-scopes while still maintaining proper eye relief.

We have a unique, reversible Picatinny rail scope mount for the Ruger 10/22 rim fire rifle that can be installed in two positions. In the forward position it accommodates the longer full size scopes, but when the mount is reversed, a mini-scope can be mounted further back to obtain a full field of view.

We installed this Picatinny rail mount on several of our Ruger 10/22s and mounted a variety of fixed and variable power mini-scopes using different types and brands of scope rings. The result of these experiments were several Ruger 10/22 packages, including this kit, which offer great values for hunters and target shooters.

Leave the power set on 3x or 4x in the field and you’re ready for close-in fast moving targets. As the target range increases, turn the magnification ring up to a higher power and you are ready for longer shots. For those really long shots at smaller targets, steady the rifle on a solid rest and turn the power ring up to the full 9X power.
